---
import Layout from '../layouts/layout.astro';
const base = '/dylan-purbrick';
---

<Layout title="Dylan Purbrick | Professional Reflection" activeTab="uni">
  <div class="max-w-4xl">
    <header class="mb-20 border-b border-slate-200 pb-12">
        <h1 class="text-6xl font-black uppercase tracking-tighter mb-4">Professional Reflection</h1>
        <p class="text-brand-purple font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.4em]">Section_04 // Internship Analysis & Career Application</p>
    </header>

    <div class="space-y-24">
        <section>
            <h2 class="text-brand-orange font-black uppercase text-xs tracking-[0.3em] mb-8">01 // Internship Reality vs. Expectations</h2>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 font-neue text-slate-700">
                <div class="space-y-4">
                    <h3 class="text-[10px] font-black uppercase tracking-widest text-slate-400">Pre-Internship Expectations</h3>
                    <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed italic">
                        "I expected the work to include elements of hands-on experience... and that this would be a great opportunity to expand my knowledge to further my career."
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="space-y-4">
                    <h3 class="text-[10px] font-black uppercase tracking-widest text-slate-400">The Reality</h3>
                    <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">
                        The experience aligned well with my expectations, though there was more paperwork than initially anticipated. The people were friendlier and the environment was more welcoming than imagined.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="bg-white/50 p-12 rounded-2xl border border-slate-200">
            <h2 class="text-brand-orange font-black uppercase text-xs tracking-[0.3em] mb-12 text-center">02 // Core Professional Lessons</h2>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-16">
                <div>
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-black uppercase mb-4">Adaptability & Change</h3>
                    <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
                        I learned that being open to change and being adaptable are essential. When things do not go perfectly to plan, an engineer must effectively manage the task no matter how off-track the project goes.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-black uppercase mb-4">Effective Communication</h3>
                    <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
                        Clear communication—or "being talkative"—is vital to prevent misunderstandings that derail projects. It builds better team relationships and makes it easier to reach out when issues arise.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2 class="text-brand-orange font-black uppercase text-xs tracking-[0.3em] mb-12">03 // Value Proposition</h2>
            <p class="text-2xl font-black uppercase text-slate-800 mb-12 leading-tight">
                "A versatile, process-oriented technical resource capable of translating complex engineering knowledge into clear, accessible documentation."
            </p>
            
            <div class="space-y-8 font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-wider text-slate-500">
                <div class="flex gap-6 border-l-2 border-brand-purple pl-6">
                    <span class="text-brand-orange font-bold">[01]</span>
                    <p>Process Improvement: Reformatting customer visitation records into traceability tables in Excel for better tracking.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="flex gap-6 border-l-2 border-brand-purple pl-6">
                    <span class="text-brand-orange font-bold">[02]</span>
                    <p>Systems Implementation: Leading internal discussions on the adoption of Autodesk Vault Pro into the company workflow.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="flex gap-6 border-l-2 border-brand-purple pl-6">
                    <span class="text-brand-orange font-bold">[03]</span>
                    <p>Technical Writing: Authored user manuals for the Schenck Balancing rotor and centrifuge stripping process.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="border-t-4 border-industrial-black pt-20">
            <h2 class="text-brand-orange font-black uppercase text-xs tracking-[0.3em] mb-8">04 // Cover Letter Archive</h2>
            <div class="bg-white p-12 md:p-20 shadow-xl font-neue text-slate-800 leading-relaxed space-y-8 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
                <div class="flex justify-between items-start border-b pb-8">
                    <div>
                        <p class="font-black uppercase text-lg">Dylan Purbrick</p>
                        <p class="text-xs text-slate-400">Graduate Engineer Applicant</p>
                    </div>
                    <p class="text-xs font-mono">10/03/2026</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="space-y-4">
                    <p class="font-bold">RE: GRADUATE ENGINEER PROGRAM APPLICATION // Industrus Engineering</p>
                    <p>Dear Hiring Manager,</p>
                    <p>
                        I am writing to apply for the Graduate Engineer Program at Industrus Engineering. I am currently finishing my final year of a Bachelor of Engineering (Honours) in Mechatronic Engineering at UTS while working as an Engineering Assistant at Keith Engineering.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        At Keith Engineering, I am responsible for final quality checks of manufacturing drawings, ensuring technical accuracy to prevent material waste. I systematically cross-reference CAD models against Bills of Materials (BOM) to catch discrepancies early. This process has taught me that accountability is about ensuring the final product is safe and efficient.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        My role also requires acting as a bridge between technical drafting teams and clients, translating complex engineering data into accessible project costs and quotes. Furthermore, I have demonstrated innovation through university projects, such as designing print-in-place additive manufacturing tools with tight tolerance control.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        As a co-founder of the UTS MechSoc, I focused on delegating tasks and keeping teams motivated. I am eager to bring this collaborative mindset and my hands-on background to Industrus Engineering's future projects.
                    </p>
                    <p>Best Regards,<br/><span class="font-black uppercase">Dylan Purbrick</span></p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
